				\begin{document}$$ {b}_j\left(\overline{X}\right)= \exp \left(\frac{-{\left(\overline{X}-{\mu}_j\right)}^2}{2{\sigma}_j^2}\right),\kern0.5em \mathrm{f}\mathrm{o}\mathrm{r}\ j = 1,\ 2,\dots, q $$\end{document}where Î¼j is the respective center of the jth neuron in the hidden layer and Ïj is the wide of the Gaussian potential function of the jth neuron in the hidden layer.

